      • testCircularDependencyDetection

        public void testCircularDependencyDetection()
                                     throws BuildFileParseException,
                                            NoSuchBuildTargetException
        Creates the following graph (assume all / and \ indicate downward pointing arrows): 
                 A
       /   \
     B       C <----|
   /   \   /        |
 D       E          |
   \   /            |
     F --------------
        Note that there is a circular dependency from C -> E -> F -> C that should be caught by the parser.
        Throws:
        BuildFileParseException
        NoSuchBuildTargetException
